      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Members of the Cooks and Walters\nUnion still presist in patroling the walk\nin front of the Ondawa Inn. This\nmorning warrant was issued for the\narrest of F. NJ. Hooper and F. M. Nc\nkenna on the charge of disorderly\nconduct. Hooper and McKenna are\ntwo of the three men arrested last week\non the same charge. They were taken\nto the station and compelled to give \"a\nbond of $50 each for their appearance\nin police court No difficulty was found\nin procuring the bond\n\n\n1t appears that the union will persist\nin keeping the union pickets in front Of\nthe Inn until the matter is taken be-\nfore higher court. Last Saturday\nJudge Hinkle held in police court that\nit was a case of disorderly conduct to\npatrol the sidewalk in front of the Inn\nwhen told to move on by the officers."
    }
